dellNetSysComponentMib.name: dellNetSysComponentMib
dellNetSysComponentMib.description: Dell Networking OS System component MIB. Dell Networking OS System component allow user to view the SW information of a component in the system. Currently, the available component information that are avaibale are 1) CAM Entries on linecard - Overall system CAM usage table - L2 Ingress or Egress CAM Usage - L3 Ingress or Egress CAM Usage - L3Ext Table CAM Usage (Specific to S-series L3 tables-Broadcom pltforms)

camUsageTable.description: A table of general CAM usages table.

camUsageEntry.description: A table of CAM usage table. The table show the different partition of CAM

camUsageSlot.description: The slot number of linecard where the CAM is located

camUsageTotal.description: The total cam size allocated to this CAM partition

camUsageUsed.description: The total cam used or configured to this CAM partition

camUsageL3ExtHostTotal.name: camUsageL3ExtHostTotal
camUsageL3ExtHostTotal.description: The total cam size allocated to layer 3 Host table. Host table is shared by IPv4,IPv6 unicast host route entries (ARP) and IPv4,IPv6 Multicast entries. The usage reflects sum of all these entries

camUsageL3ExtHostUsed.name: camUsageL3ExtHostUsed

camUsageL3ExtLPMTotal.name: camUsageL3ExtLPMTotal

camUsageL3ExtLPMUsed.name: camUsageL3ExtLPMUsed
camUsageL3ExtLPMUsed.description: The total cam size used in layer 3 Longest Prefix Match table. The LPM table is shared by IPv4,Ipv6 unicast route entries.The usage reflects sum of IPv4 and v6 unicast route entries.
